missing_optimizations: Use of std::comp_ellint_1 instead of boost_like_ellint_1

reasons_for_missed_optimizations: The LLM version retained the concept of simulating a heavier Boost implementation by using boost_like_ellint_1, which is unnecessary since the hand-optimized code directly utilizes the standard library function for improved performance.
additional_insights: The LLM version uniquely improved performance through the precomputation of the k values, avoiding the recalculation within the inner loop.
